last_episode_to_air.name: Mother of All Finales
last_episode_to_air.overview: The finalists design their dream runway looks with the salon adn perform with an icon. It's a family affair but only one competitor will be crowned the new First Child of Drag.

name: Call Me Mother
overview: Three drag legends, Peppermint, Crystal and Barbada adopt the next generation of talent into their new drag houses and mentor them through the mother of all drag competitions. Each performer competes for the title, ‘First Child of Drag’, through a series of challenges that elevate, test and showcase their best drag.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: The series first premiered on OUTtv’s Canadian and U.S. platforms on Oct. 25, as well as the U.K. and Ireland through Free TV.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Two days after the first season finale, OutTV announced the renewal of the series for a second season.

episodes.name: Adoptions
episodes.overview: It's Adoption Day. Ten drag artists audition to join one of three newly formed Drag Houses.

episodes.name: Let Them Eat Cake
episodes.overview: In honor of Mother’s Day, the competitors are challenged to decorate cakes inspired by Mother and then design their family runway – Marie Antoinette based ‘Let Them Eat Cake’ confections.

episodes.name: Tantrums & Tiaras
episodes.overview: Still reeling from last week’s elimination, the Houses quickly refocus their efforts for the Tantrums & Tiaras pageant.

episodes.name: Modern Horrors
episodes.overview: With one House leading the competition, everyone is challenged to reenact a scene from a classic horror film. The costumes might be black and white but the families are feeling all sorts of technicolor as the competition takes a shocking turn.

episodes.name: The Roast of Yo Mama
episodes.overview: The tables are turned on Miss Peppermint, Crystal and Barbada as the artists prepare to Roast their Mothers. One of the world’s most famous Drag Kings stops by to deliver a masterclass in the art of ‘punching up’ and Burn Baby Burn looks heat up the runway.

episodes.name: Out of the Darkness
episodes.overview: Not one, but two members of international drag royalty swing by as the five remaining artists get dolled up and take a theatrical journey to London’s West End for a very special performance that everybody will be talking about.

episodes.name: Turbulence & Business Class
episodes.overview: The final four struggle with sky-high emotions and sky-high challenges. Their brand pitches for Matthew Camp are business class but the competitors' relationships are heading for coach.

episodes.name: The Mother of All Finales
episodes.overview: The Grand Finale is the motherlode of drag performances. The finalists share the stage with Mother in three iconic lip syncs.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: The series first premiered on OUTtv’s Canadian and U.S. platforms on Oct. 25, as well as the U.K. and Ireland through Free TV.

episodes.name: Adoptions
episodes.overview: Drag mothers Miss Peppermint (House of Dulcet), Crystal (House of Glass) and Barbada (House of Harmonie) are back for another battle.

episodes.name: Family Day
episodes.overview: The new members of the Houses of Dulcet, Harmonie and Glass struggle to create their first picture-perfect house runway and family talent show. Not everyone is blending well with their make-up or their new siblings.

episodes.name: Safety Dance
episodes.overview: Still spinning from a tough elimination, the newly-bonded Houses play bingo with iconic special guest Alaska. Farra N Hyte choreographs her latest show while kinks and corsets come out on the Safe Sex runway.

episodes.name: Of Monsters and Media
episodes.overview: The artists double down on their drive to win as they face swap in a make-up challenge. The Mothers call in celebrity friends to give a much-needed shot of support and web nightmares come true on the runway.

episodes.name: Might Have Been Me
episodes.overview: The competitors start to feel the burn as they warm up for the Rost & Toast. Winner of S1, Toddy, Joins in for some comedy coaching and WigZaddy leads a hair-raising dragvantage.

episodes.name: Leave It on the Stage
episodes.overview: With only two eliminations until the finale, the artists dive into Sci-Fi Film Duets with a twist: it's a mother swap! Lucinda Miu leads a dragvantage that has everyone in stitches.

episodes.name: Sell It
episodes.overview: With one last chance to sell themselves and win a place in the finale, the artists dig into their drag branding for the Merchable Me showcase. Despite Mother's guidance, some competitors start to question their sales skills.

episodes.name: Family Reunion
episodes.overview: The final four are primed to battle for the crown. Celebrate the highs and lows of their journey to the title, reunite with favorite competitors, find out who is most likely to start a feud and who is the biggest flirt. It's a family reunion, drag style.
